metadata.name: Sap song. Part II #19
metadata.description:
This artwork corresponds to the 2nd part of the ‚ÄòSap song‚Äô series. It seeks to expand the concept from new visual and sound variants.

Audiovisual generative artwork that continues with the proposal of excessive flows of organic forms. In time, frenetic arpeggios and populations of colorful plants with spiral flowers are emerging, all organized in their own way. And the sap again sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. ‚ÄúEnredo coral‚Äù
II. ‚ÄúRecitativo libre‚Äù
III. ‚ÄúCoda hacia la ra√≠z‚Äù

Original samplers of cello pizzicatos, marimba, music box, piano, and multiphonics of clarinet and flute.

metadata.name: Story Of Shapes #15
metadata.description:
This p5js Generative Token tells one "Story Of Shapes" 

Shapes have different meanings depending on cultures, themes, languages, countries, people, etc. 

Through these tokens, I tell you one story, the one of Teiyu Goto, Sony Designer :

In a 2010 interview with Famitsu Magazine, Goto said he was well aware that ‚Äúother game companies at the time assigned alphabet letters or colors to the buttons. We wanted something simple to remember, which is why we went with icons or symbols, and I came up with the triangle-circle-X-square combination immediately after.‚Äù A name is just a name until you impart some meaning to it.

Goto wanted to be memorable but he also wanted to make sense, at least in his own mind. ‚ÄúI gave each symbol a meaning and a color,‚Äù he states in the same interview. ‚ÄúThe triangle refers to viewpoint; I had it represent one‚Äôs head or direction and made it green. Square refers to a piece of paper; I had it represent menus or documents and made it pink. The circle and X represent ‚Äòyes‚Äô or ‚Äòno‚Äô decision-making, and I made them red and blue, respectively. People thought those colors were mixed up, and I had to reinforce to management that that‚Äôs what I wanted.‚Äù 

You understand, this is only ONE Story.

Give us YOUR Story.

St4rfcuk

By the way, You can click left button to save a .PNG file.

Features : 
- Shapes counter
- 20 Color Palettes
- Random Shapes & Colors

metadata.name: Flowers #55
metadata.description:
This project is inspired by natural flowers.
Flowers and foliage in the piece are arranged randomly, but they follow a regular pattern, as flowers do as they grow.
Initially, flowers are produced randomly and without color. Afterwards, the pieces are painted according to the color palettes, so that viewers can feel the effect of colors.
Each piece is processed until the frame part is reached.

Fully generated by p5.js

Press 's' to get a 3000x3000 px PNG file.

metadata.name: ZOOM (4hwf) #85
metadata.description:
"Das System l√§sst keine √úberraschung zu. √úberraschung ist Ausdruck partieller Unkenntnis. √úberraschung weist auf Mangel von Wissen hin, deutet Leerstellen an. Bisher hatten sie keine Leerstellen festgestellt." ‚Äî Herbert W. Franke

ZOOM explores linear scaling of pixels by zooming into a noisy framebuffer. Various zoom levels are composed one below the other, becoming a cinematic animation through iteration of the hue values of the pixels in the framebuffer.

In Gedenken an Herbert W. Franke
Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Landstreicher #32
metadata.description:
A couple of strokes wandering through the landscapes.

The space is randomly cut in segments on both axis. Some of the resulting rectangles are randomly selected to be paired. A second layer with similar ingredients is placed on top.

* stroke size is randomly chosen and gets distorted along the way
* spacing between the hatches is relative to the stroke size
* speed of the strokes is randomly chosen for each line
* stroke color is randomly distorted
* the background noise is randomly generated
* 12 palettes with 2 colors

100% generative, no pngs. The source code is published here: https://github.com/sektionschef/landstreicher
